00:24:00.123 --> 00:24:03.995
I have replaced it with a P.
So the same definition except

00:24:03.995 --> 00:24:07.230
I'm using mixed strategies
instead of pure strategies.

00:24:07.230 --> 00:24:11.869
But an implication of our
lesson is what?

00:24:11.869 --> 00:24:16.201
It's that if P_i* is
part of a Nash Equilibrium--so

00:24:16.201 --> 00:24:20.460
if Pi* is a best response to
what everyone else is doing,

00:24:20.460 --> 00:24:24.366
P_-i* --,
then each of the pure

00:24:24.366 --> 00:24:29.542
strategies involved in
P_i* must itself be a

00:24:29.542 --> 00:24:35.321
best response.
So an implication of the lesson

00:24:35.321 --> 00:24:40.250
is, the lesson implies the
following.

00:24:40.250 --> 00:24:45.600
If P_i* of a
particular strategy is positive,

00:24:45.600 --> 00:24:50.257
so in other words,
I'm using this strategy in my

00:24:50.257 --> 00:24:57.168
mix,
then that strategy is also a

00:24:57.168 --> 00:25:07.220
best response to what everyone
else is doing.

